# TypeScript / JavaScript

- Strong typing — avoid `any`; prefer explicit types and discriminated unions.
- Immutable patterns (spread/`readonly`), avoid in-place mutation.
- Async correctness — await promises, handle rejections, no floating promises.
- Node/web security — validate input, avoid injection, no secrets in client code.
- Tests with the project's framework (Vitest/Jest/Playwright); 80%+ coverage.
